Why EBS / Volume issues are common
Root volume full: Logs / temp files / applications filled disk → OS cannot boot
File system corruption: Improper shutdown, snapshot restore issues, or write failures
Volume attachment issues: Wrong device name / leftover mounts → boot fails
High I/O / heavy utilization during boot: For example, if cloud-init downloads too many packages on small volume

So yes, in practice, high volume utilization / full root disk + file system corruption is the #1 reason Linux EC2 doesn’t start.

3️⃣ How to quickly check if volume is the problem
Get system log from console:
Look for messages like No space left on device, ext4-fs error, kernel panic

Detach & mount volume on another instance:

Check disk usage:
df -h /mnt/recovery
Check filesystem integrity:
sudo fsck /dev/xvdf1
Clean up / repair → reattach → try boot

💡 TL;DR:

High volume usage / corrupted root volume = most common Linux EC2 startup failure
Others: cloud-init failure, bad AMI, AWS infra issues, but less frequent

